<section id="run-level-ro-crate-provenance-with-nf-prov" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="run-level-ro-crate-provenance-with-nf-prov">Run-Level RO-Crate: Provenance with nf-prov</h2>
<p>The pipeline-level RO-Crate describes your workflow as a static artifact. Run-level provenance captures what actually happened in a specific execution — which input files, which container versions, which parameters, what outputs, and when.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://github.com/nextflow-io/nf-prov"><code>nf-prov</code> plugin</a> handles this in Nextflow.</p>
<section id="enabling-nf-prov" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="enabling-nf-prov">Enabling nf-prov</h3>
<p>Add to your <code>nextflow.config</code>:</p>
